<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-14T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-14T20:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1915: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">William Phillips</persName>, Personal
                                Representative of President <persName>Roosevelt</persName> in
                                India</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-14T21:00:00-04:00">April 14,
                                    1943—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>199. Your 278, April 11. While I have no objection to your making the
                            request referred to in the first paragraph of your 257, April 2, 4 p.m.,
                            on a purely personal basis, I believe it would be inopportune to adopt
                            the suggestion in the final paragraph of that telegram.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>